F108320899.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108320899.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20makers%20of%20'Shaitaan'%20organized%20a%20special%20screening%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20which%20was%20attended%20by%20R.%20Madhavan%2C%20Suriya%2C%20Jyotika%2C%20and%20Kartik%20Aaryan%2C%20among%20others.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fjaideep-ahlawat-pays-a-special-tribute-to-the-late-actor-irrfan-khan-at-the-special-screening-of-shaitaan-watch%2Farticleshow%2F108320899.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20finance%20professional%20fired%20over%20watching%20pornography%20at%20work%20said%20it%20was%20because%20his%20computer%20was%20infected%20by%20a%20Trojan%20virus%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Asian%20man%20scrolls%20on%20his%20phone%20at%20work.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eaae03ce7f1785b2e7b0d3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225733%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Shanghai%20High%20Court%20reported%20that%20a%2041-year-old%20financial%20services%20professional%20was%20fired%20after%20watching%20pornography%20at%20work.%3Cp%3EOscar%20Wong%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%2041-year-old%20client%20manager%20was%20fired%20for%20browsing%20adult%20content%20at%20work%2C%20but%20said%20it%20wasn't%20him.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Shanghai%20man%20blamed%20a%20virus%20that%20infected%20his%20computer%20or%20his%20own%20colleagues%2C%20per%20the%20local%20court.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20sued%20his%20employer%20for%20wrongful%20termination%2C%20and%20wanted%20%2443%2C000%20in%20damages.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20financial%20services%20worker%20in%20Shanghai%20who%20was%20fired%20for%20browsing%20pornographic%20websites%20at%20work%20has%20sued%20his%20former%20employer%2C%20blaming%20a%20virus%20that%20infected%20his%20computer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2041-year-old%20client%20relationship%20manager%2C%20identified%20by%20the%20municipal%20high%20court%20by%20his%20surname%20Yang%2C%20sought%20%2443%2C000%20in%20damages%20and%20said%20his%20contract%20was%20wrongfully%20terminated%2C%20authorities%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweibo.com%2Fttarticle%2Fp%2Fshow%3Fid%3D2309405009221782470997%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20report%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChinese%20courts%20do%20not%20typically%20name%20prosecutors%20and%20defendants%20in%20full%20for%20civil%20cases%20that%20are%20not%20high-profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYang%20had%20worked%20for%20five%20years%20under%20his%20employer%20and%20earned%20about%20%242%2C360%20a%20month%20until%20he%20was%20fired%20in%20August%202022%2C%20per%20the%20Shanghai%20High%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20monthly%20salary%20in%20urban%20Shanghai%20was%20around%20%241%2C700%20that%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shpt.gov.cn%2Fshpt%2Ffy-fyzx%2F20230629%2F903363.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E6%259C%25AC%25E5%25B8%25822022%25E5%25B9%25B4%25E5%25BA%25A6%25E5%2585%25A8%2C%25E8%25B0%2583%25E6%2595%25B4%25E4%25B8%25BA7310%25E5%2585%2583%252F%25E6%259C%2588%25E3%2580%2582%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elatest%20government%20statistics.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYang's%20employer%20said%20that%20Yang%20had%20breached%20his%20contract%20%E2%80%94%20which%20prohibits%20employees%20from%20consuming%20pornography%20at%20work%20%E2%80%94%20by%20accessing%20%26quot%3Blittle%20movies%26quot%3B%20on%20his%20work%20computer.%20The%20term%20is%20a%20euphemism%20in%20China%20for%20explicit%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Yang%20submitted%20company%20records%20that%20showed%20his%20colleagues%20often%20downloaded%20movies%20or%20shows%20on%20their%20work%20computers%20outside%20business%20hours.%20He%20said%20that%20this%20may%20have%20caused%20his%20computer%20to%20become%20infected%20by%20Trojan%20malware%2C%20per%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20showed%20the%20court%20a%20photo%20of%20his%20office%2C%20which%20was%20an%20open%20space%20with%20no%20speakers%2C%20and%20said%20such%20a%20working%20environment%20was%20not%20conducive%20for%20consuming%20pornographic%20material%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20Yang%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Blittle%20movies%26quot%3B%20thus%20must%20have%20been%20watched%20by%20someone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYang%20admitted%20to%20an%20adult%20site%20membership%20in%20his%20'personal%20reflection'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYang's%20employer%2C%20who%20was%20not%20named%2C%20fired%20back%20with%20internet%20records%20that%20showed%20the%20adult%20site%20browsing%20was%20performed%20while%20Yang%20sent%20files%20to%20colleagues%20and%20actively%20performed%20work%20tasks%2C%20indicating%20he%20was%20using%20the%20computer%20at%20the%20time%2C%20per%20the%20Shanghai%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20showed%20the%20court%20a%20transcript%20from%20a%20messaging%20chat%20group%2C%20where%20Yang%20wrote%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bpersonal%20reflection%26quot%3B%20submission%20to%20his%20boss%20that%20he%20had%20signed%20up%20for%20a%20membership%20on%20an%20adult%20content%20website%20and%20struggled%20with%20self-discipline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20reflection%2C%20Yang%20said%20he%20would%20have%20to%20repeatedly%20return%20to%20the%20website%20to%20click%20on%20links%2C%20allowing%20him%20to%20earn%20points%20and%20maintain%20his%20membership%20status%2C%20per%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20taken%20during%20Yang's%20hearing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65eaaf7690413ab8e1da9d65%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22416%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20photo%20taken%20during%20Yang's%20hearing.%3Cp%3EScreenshot%2FShanghai%20High%20Court%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Xuhui%20Court%20ruled%20that%20Yang%20clearly%20breached%20his%20contract%20and%20struck%20down%20his%20claim%20for%20%2443%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20now-fired%20client%20manager%20was%20awarded%20%241%2C090%20for%20five%20days%20of%20paid%20leave%20that%20he%20didn't%20take%20in%202021%2C%20which%20Yang%20had%20included%20in%20his%20lawsuit%2C%20per%20the%20municipal%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20Yang%20has%20sued%20his%20employer%20for%20the%20same%20firing.%20He%20tried%20to%20ask%20for%20%2447%2C000%20in%20damages%20in%20November%202022%20but%20was%20only%20given%20%241%2C500%20for%20leftover%20PTO%20that%20he%20didn't%20take%20that%20year%2C%20per%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20remote%20work%20saw%20a%20striking%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20using%20company%20devices%20to%20access%20adult%20websites.%20In%202020%2C%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-porn-work-computers-remote-hr-legal-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadmitted%20to%20such%20acts%20grew%20six-fold%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20to%202019%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20by%20software%20company%20Netskope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECybersecurity%20firm%20Kaspersky%20reported%20that%2051%25%20of%20the%206%2C000%20employees%20it%20surveyed%20in%202020%20said%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-people-watching-porn-on-work-computers-coronavirus-remote-work-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewatched%20adult%20content%20on%20the%20devices%20they%20use%20for%20work.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinance-worker-fired-watch