iums%20on%20bankruptcy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20first%20came%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20that%20started%20in%202020%3B%20the%20second%20came%20after%20the%20West%20imposed%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%20over%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%202022.%20The%20moratoriums%20expired%20in%202021%20and%20late%202022%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIlya%20Torosov%2C%20Russia's%20first%20deputy%20economy%20minister%2C%20told%20Kommersant%20that%20this%20is%20merely%20a%20return%20to%20pre-pandemic%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOn-the-ground%20difficulties%20in%20Russia%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20uptick%20in%20corporate%20bankruptcies%20highlights%20the%20difficulties%20faced%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20Russia.%20It%20also%20stands%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20rosy%20official%20statistics%20the%20Kremlin%20releases%2C%20which%20show%20that%20Russia's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftass.com%2Feconomy%2F1743227%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGDP%20grew%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%203.6%25%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20government%20spending%2C%20Russia's%20wartime%20economy%20is%20resilient%20%E2%80%94%20but%20high%20interest%20rates%20are%20biting.%20The%20Bank%20of%20Russia%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-economy-central-bank-hikes-interest-rates-war-inflation-markets-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehiked%20interest%20rates%20up%20to%2016%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20cool%20the%20economy%20and%20tame%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20are%20experiencing%20problems%20with%20refinancing%20as%20the%20effects%20of%20monetary%20tightening%20are%20starting%20to%20kick%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Bartosz%20Sawicki%2C%20a%20market%20analyst%20at%20Conotoxia%2C%20a%20Polish%20fintech%20firm%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20war-related%20sectors%20such%20as%20arms%20production%2C%20the%20Russian%20economy%20looks%20%26quot%3