%20sources%20said%20that%20a%20formal%20announcement%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20alliance%20could%20be%20made%20in%20the%20next%20few%20days%2C%20most%20probably%20on%20March%2012%20when%20Union%20home%20minister%20and%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20right-hand%20man%20Amit%20Shah%20is%20likely%20to%20visit%20the%20state.%20%E2%80%9COnly%20the%20seat-sharing%20arrangement%20has%20to%20be%20finalised.%20The%20BJP%20wants%2013%20out%20of%20Odisha%E2%80%99s%2021%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20and%20at%20least%2054%20assembly%20seats.%20This%20may%20not%20be%20acceptable%20to%20the%20BJD.%20Then%20there%20is%20the%20issue%20of%20seat%20selection%2C%20which%20could%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20trickier%20than%20it%20seems.%20Once%20these%20things%20are%20sorted%20out%2C%20a%20formal%20announcement%20will%20be%20made%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20senior%20BJP%20leader%20who%20did%20not%20wish%20to%20be%20identified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJD%20presently%20has%2012%20Lok%20Sabha%20members%20and%20accounts%20for%20112%20of%20the%20147%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20assembly.%20The%20BJP%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20holds%20eight%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20including%20all%20five%20in%20western%20Odisha%2C%20its%20traditional%20stronghold.%20With%2022%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%2C%20it%20also%20enjoys%20the%20honour%20of%20being%20the%20main%20opposition%20party%2C%20a%20title%20earlier%20held%20by%20the%20Congress%20which%20has%20now%20been%20reduced%20to%20just%20nine%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20assembly.%20The%20Congress%20holds%20just%20one%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%20%E2%80%93%20Koraput%20%E2%80%93%20in%20southern%20Odisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20alliance%20and%20seat-sharing%20issues%20being%20discussed%20at%20the%20highest%20level%2C%20state%20leaders%20of%20both%20parties%20are%20being%20extremely%20cautious%20in%20their%20reactions.%20Speaking%20to%20local%20TV%20channels%2C%20senior%20BJD%20leader%20and%20former%20minister%20Debi%20Prasad%20Mishra%20tried%20to%20side-step%20the%20issue%20of%20an%20alliance.%20However%2C%20asked%20repeatedly%20about%20it%20after%20the%20meeting%20at%20Naveen%20Niwas%2C%20he%20vaguely%20remarked%20that%20%E2%80%9Ceverything%20was%20discussed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMixed%20emotions%20in%20the%20BJP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EState%20BJP%20leaders%20have%20been%20more%20forthright%20while%20commenting%20on%20the%20issue.%20Former%20party%20MLA%20Pradeep%20Purohit%20not%20only%20admitted%20that%20the%20chances%20of%20a%20revival%20of%20the%20alliance%20between%20the%20two%20parties%20appeared%20bright%2C%20but%20also%20exuded%20confidence%20about%20the%20BJP%20gaining%20much%20more%20than%20the%20BJD%20from%20this.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20it%20happens%2C%20which%20seems%20almost%20certain%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%20coalition%20government%20again%20and%20we%20will%20be%20back%20in%20power.%20Besides%2C%20it%20is%20almost%20certain%20that%20the%20BJP%20will%20win%20more%20assembly%20seats%20than%20it%20did%20in%202019.%20What%20is%20most%20important%20from%20our%20point%20of%20view%20is%20that%20all%20the%2021%20Lok%20Sabha%20MPs%20from%20the%20state%20will%20support%20the%20BJP-led%20government%20at%20the%20Centre%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Purohit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20not%20all%20leaders%20of%20the%20party%20share%20his%20optimism%20and%20enthusiasm.%20Mohan%20Majhi%2C%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20tribal%20face%20and%20its%20deputy%20leader%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%2C%20is%20apprehensive%20that%20the%20hard%20work%20the%20party%20cadre%20did%20in%20several%20constituencies%20for%20the%20last%20five%20years%20to%20strengthen%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20base%20may%20go%20waste.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20be%20sure%20if%20we%20will%20get%20those%20seats.%20The%20truth%20is%20we%20have%20been%20working%20over%20time%20to%20strengthen%20our%20position%20across%20the%20state.%20The%20BJD%20was%20our%20main%20enemy%20but%20now%20the%20whole%20equation%20is%20going%20to%20change.%20Though%20the%20central%20leadership%E2%80%99s%20decision%20has%20to%20be%20respected%2C%20there%20is%20no%20denying%20the%20anger%20among%20our%20workers%20as%20we%20are%20going%20to%20join%20hands%20with%20the%20party%20which%20had%20ditched%20us%20in%202009%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Majhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMajhi%2C%20however%2C%20admitted%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20central%20leadership%20has%20its%20own%20compulsions.%20%E2%80%9COur%20slogan%20this%20time%20is%20%3Cem%3Eabki%20baar%2C%20char%20sau%20paar%3C%2Fem%3E%20(let%E2%80%99s%20cross%20the%20400-seat%20mark%20this%20time).%20For%20this%20goal%20to%20be%20realised%2C%20we%20may%20have%20to%20make%20some%20compromises.%20We%20may%20need%20to%20revive%20old%20alliances%20and%20also%20win%20new%20allies.%20But%20it%20will%20be%20extremely%20difficult%20to%20convince%20the%20ordinary%20workers%20who%20have%20been%20working%20round%20the%20year%20for%20the%20growth%20of%20the%20party%20in%20the%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20leader.%20Most%20BJP%20leaders%20in%20the%20state%2C%20though%20unwilling%20to%20go%20on%20record%20at%20this%20juncture%2C%20share%20Majhi%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20cadre%20rebellion%20in%20the%20state%20in%20the%20event%20of%20the%20BJD-BJP%20alliance%20being%20revived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20alliance%20and%20a%20break%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20denying%20that%20the%20BJD-BJP%20alliance%20that%20came%20into%20existence%20in%201998%2C%20just%20a%20year%20after%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20regional%20party%2C%20was%20a%20marriage%20of%20convenience%2C%20as%20there%20was%20no%20ideological%20match%20between%20the%20two%20parties.%20The%20BJD%2C%20being%20a%20fledgling%20party%2C%20found%20it%20politically%20wise%20to%20join%20hands%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20was%20on%20the%20upswing%20at%20the%20time.%20The%20fact%20that%20Atal%20Behari%20Vajpayee%2C%20whose%20liberal%20views%20made%20him%20acceptable%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%2C%20was%20the%20top%20leader%20of%20the%20BJP%20made%20the%20decision%20of%20an%20alliance%20easier%20for%20the%20regional%20party%20which%20was%20named%20after%20Biju%20Patnaik%2C%20the%20father%20of%20Naveen%20and%20two-time%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20state%20whose%20secular%20credentials%20were%20never%20in%20doubt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20important%20factor%20that%20dictated%20BJD%E2%80%99s%20choice%20of%20its%20ally%20was%20that%20it%20treated%20the%20Congress%20as%20its%20prime%20enemy%20right%20from%20the%20beginning.%20The%20BJD-BJP%20alliance%20also%20swept%20to%20power%20in%20Odisha%20in%202000%20on%20an%20anti-Congress%20plank.%20The%20coalition%20had%20then%20sought%20to%20expose%20the%20corruption%20and%20inefficiency%20of%20the%20incumbent%20Congress%20government%2C%20which%20had%20completely%20mismanaged%20the%20relief%20and%20rehabilitation%20work%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%201999%20super-cyclone%20which%20had%20devastated%20the%20entire%20coastal%20belt%20of%20Odisha%2C%20leaving%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20people%20dead%20and%20lakhs%20homeless.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20there%20could%20be%20no%20question%20of%20aligning%20with%20the%20Congress%2C%20and%20BJP%20became%20the%20ally%20of%20the%20regional%20party%20almost%20by%20default.%20The%20two-party%20coalition%20ran%20the%20state%20for%20nearly%20nine%20years%2C%20but%20the%20going%20was%20never%20completely%20smooth%20given%20their%20differences%20over%20a%20number%20of%20issues.%20Senior%20BJP%20leaders%20like%20former%20Union%20minister%20Jual%20Oram%20openly%20criticised%20the%20chief%20minister%20when%20the%20state%20government%20signed%20a%20memorandum%20of%20understanding%20with%20South%20Korean%20steel%20behemoth%20Pohang%20Steel%20Company%20(POSCO)%20for%20setting%20up%20a%2012%20million%20tonne%20capacity%20steel%20plant%20in%20Jagatsinghpur%20district%20and%20the%20company%20started%20eyeing%20iron%20ore%20reserves%20in%20Khandadhar%20which%20is%20part%20of%20Sundergarh%2C%20Oram%E2%80%99s%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EState%20BJP%20leaders%20also%20detested%20Patnaik%E2%80%99s%20indifference%20towards%20them%20as%20he%20preferred%20to%20deal%20with%20their%20central%20party%20leaders.%20Things%20came%20to%20a%20head%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%202008%20Kandhamal%20communal%20riots%2C%20which%20took%20a%20heavy%20toll%20on%20Patnaik%E2%80%99s%20secular%20image.%20Soon%20the%20chief%20minister%20realised%20that%20his%20alliance%20partner%20had%20become%20a%20liability%20and%20the%20coalition%20was%20becoming%20increasingly%20unsustainable.%20Though%20it%20is%20said%20that%20the%2011-year-old%20BJD-BJP%20alliance%20collapsed%20ahead%20of%20the%202009%20elections%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20seat%20sharing%2C%20it%20is%20an%20open%20secret%20that%20Patnaik%20had%20made%20up%20his%20mind%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20contested%20the%202009%20elections%20separately%20and%20the%20results%20made%20it%20more%20than%20obvious%20that%20all%20this%20time%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20been%20piggyback-riding%20on%20the%20BJD%20in%20Odisha.%20While%20the%20BJD%20came%20to%20power%20with%20a%20comfortable%20majority%2C%20the%20BJP%20could%20win%20just%20six%20seats%20in%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20147-strong%20assembly.%20It%20drew%20a%20blank%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20The%202014%20elections%20saw%20the%20saffron%20party%20bagging%2010%20assembly%20seats%20and%20the%20lone%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%20of%20Sundergarh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatnaik%E2%80%99s%20changing%20face%20in%20the%20Modi%20years%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%202014%20marked%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20the%20relations%20between%20the%20BJD%20and%20BJP.%20With%20the%20BJP-led%20NDA%20coming%20to%20power%20at%20the%20Centre%20with%20a%20full%20majority%2C%20Patnaik%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20the%20central%20BJP%20leadership%2C%20especially%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20improved%20substantially.%20The%20chief%20minister%20realised%20the%20importance%20of%20having%20a%20friendly%20Centre%20to%20ensure%20the%20development%20of%20the%20state.%20Even%20though%20he%20followed%20an%20avowed%20policy%20of%20maintaining%20equidistance%20from%20the%20BJP%20and%20Congress%2C%20he%20supported%20the%20NDA%20government%20on%20several%20crucial%20issues%20inside%20the%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20BJD%20backed%20the%20controversial%20Mines%20and%20Minerals%20(Development%20and%20Regulation)%20Amendment%20Bill%2C%202015%20and%20helped%20the%20NDA%20get%20it%20passed%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20where%20the%20BJP%20lacked%20the%20numbers.%20Patnaik%20was%20also%20among%20the%20first%20chief%20ministers%20of%20the%20country%20to%20welcome%20demonetisation%2C%20a%20move%20which%20faced%20criticism%20across%20the%20country.%20He%20also%20extended%20support%20to%20the%20controversial%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%20(GST)%20when%20it%20was%20facing%20flak%20from%20several%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20continued%20and%20by%20the%20time%20the%20next%20elections%20arrived%2C%20it%20was%20more%20or%20less%20clear%20that%20the%20policy%20of%20%E2%80%9Cequidistance%E2%80%9D%20was%20nothing%20but%20a%20fa%C3%A7ade%20which%20was%20becoming%20increasingly%20hard%20to%20defend.%20During%20NDA%E2%80%99s%20second%20term%20under%20Modi%2C%20the%20BJD%E2%80%99s%20support%20for%20the%20government%20at%20the%20Centre%20was%20even%20more%20obvious%2C%20with%20the%20party%20backing%20it%20on%20controversial%20issues%20like%20the%20scrapping%20of%20Article%20370%20and%20passage%20of%20the%20triple%20%3Cem%3Etalaq%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Bills.%20All%20this%20was%20done%20on%20the%20excuse%20of%20protecting%20either%20national%20interest%20or%20state%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20mutually%20convenient%20arrangement%2C%20with%20Patnaik%20getting%20generous%20financial%20assistance%20from%20the%20Centre%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20disastrous%20cyclones%20such%20as%20Fani%20which%20devastated%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20coastal%20belt.%20The%20prime%20minister%2C%20too%2C%20found%20it%20convenient%20to%20cultivate%20regional%20satraps%20like%20Patnaik%20whose%20support%20he%20needed%20in%20the%20parliament%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20need%20being%20mutual%2C%20the%20bond%20between%20the%20two%20leaders%20soon%20became%20stronger%20and%20they%20refrained%20from%20criticising%20each%20other%20even%20at%20election%20rallies%2C%20though%20their%20parties%20happened%20to%20be%20rivals%20in%20state%20politics.%20This%20embarrassed%20the%20state%20BJP%20leaders%20no%20end%2C%20but%20the%20central%20party%20leadership%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20care%20less.%20The%20occasional%20attacks%20made%20on%20the%20Patnaik%20government%20by%20leaders%20like%20Amit%20Shah%20during%20their%20visits%20to%20the%20state%20appeared%20to%20be%20more%20for%20public%20consumption.%20Now%20even%20that%20has%20stopped.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20elections%20around%20the%20corner%2C%20political%20expediency%20has%20once%20again%20taken%20precedence%20over%20principles%20and%20both%20the%20parties%20look%20almost%20set%20to%20join%20hands.%20While%20the%20BJP%20needs%20BJD%E2%80%99s%20support%20mainly%20to%20ensure%20that%20its%20Lok%20Sabha%20tally%20in%20the%20state%20goes%20up%2C%20which%20is%20crucial%20for%20the%20party%20to%20better%20its%202019%20record%20if%20not%20to%20actually%20realise%20the%20goal%20of%20400%20seats%2C%20the%20BJD%20is%20keen%20to%20retain%20its%20hold%20on%20the%20state%20so%20that%20Patnaik%20actualises%20the%20dream%20of%20becoming%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20state%20for%20the%20sixth%20time%20in%20a%20row%2C%20a%20record%20in%20itself.%20If%20sources%20are%20to%20be%20believed%2C%20a%20tacit%20understanding%20between%20the%20top%20leadership%20of%20the%20two%20parties%20has%20been%20reached%20and%20seat%20sharing%20arrangement%20will%20be%20worked%20out%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20both%20the%20parties%20out%20to%20defend%20their%20mutual%20interests%2C%20a%20marriage%20of%20convenience%20is%20once%20again%20on%20the%20cards.%20As%20political%20analyst%20Shashi%20Kant%20Mishra%20put%20it%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20could%20be%20embarrassing%20for%20the%20ordinary%20cadres%20of%20the%20two%20parties%20but%20their%20top%20leaders%20will%20be%20quite%20brazen%20about%20it.%20Jettisoning%20principles%20is%20a%20small%20sacrifice%20to%20make%20when%20bigger%20interests%20are%20involved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fashutoshmishra%5C%22%3EAshutosh%20Mishra%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20Odisha-based%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709869279000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08091041%2FGH6wRL5W4AAQK0I.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fodisha-bjp-bjd-alliance%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20state%20BJP%20leaders%20are%20worried%20that%20an%20alliance%20with%20the%20BJD%20may%20upset%20party%20cadres%2C%20the%20central%20leadership%20has%20decided%20that%20joining%20hands%20is%20the%20best%20way%20forward.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fodisha-bjp-bjd-alliance%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22On%20Women's%20Day%2C%20PM%20Modi%20announces%20Rs%20100%20discount%20on%20LPG%20cylinder%20prices%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709869150000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2019-03%2F07%2Ffull%2F1551979926-6207.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fon-women-s-day-pm-modi-announces-rs-100-discount-on-lpg-cylinder-prices-124030800091_1.html%22%2C%22s