Institute%E2%80%99s%20Democracy%20Report%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20also%20lists%20in%20the%20top%2010%20standalone%20autocratizers%20in%202023%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fv-dem.net%2F%5C%22%3Ereport.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20further%20says%20that%20India%20dropped%20down%20to%20electoral%20autocracy%20in%202018%20and%20remains%20in%20this%20category%20by%20the%20end%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEight%20out%20of%20ten%20countries%20in%20this%20group%20were%20democracies%20before%20the%20start%20of%20autocratization.%20Democracy%20broke%20down%20in%20six%20of%20those%20eight%20cases%20%E2%80%93%20The%20Comoros%2C%20Hungary%2C%20India%2C%20Mauritius%2C%20Nicaragua%2C%20and%20Serbia.%20Only%20Greece%20and%20Poland%20remain%20democracies%20in%202023.%20This%20frequency%20of%20democratic%20breakdown%20matches%20with%20a%20recent%20study%20showing%20that%2080%25%20of%20democracies%20break%20down%20if%20they%20start%20autocratizing%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%20report%20titled%20%E2%80%98Democracy%20Winning%20and%20Losing%20at%20the%20Ballot%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COver%20the%20years%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20autocratization%20process%20has%20been%20well%20documented%2C%20including%20gradual%20but%20substantial%20deterioration%20of%20freedom%20of%20expression%2C%20compromising%20independence%20of%20the%20media%2C%20crackdowns%20on%20social%20media%2C%20harassment%20of%20journalists%20critical%20of%20the%20government%2C%20as%20well%20as%20attacks%20on%20civil%20society%20and%20intimidation%20of%20the%20opposition.%20The%20ruling%20anti-pluralist%2C%20Hindu-nationalist%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20at%20the%20helm%20has%20for%20example%20used%20laws%20on%20sedition%2C%20defamation%2C%20and%20counterterrorism%20to%20silence%20critics.%20The%20BJP%20government%20undermined%20the%20constitution%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20secularism%20by%20amending%20the%20Unlaw