take%20in%20the%20company%20that%20operates%20the%20country's%20largest%20airline%2C%20IndiGo%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fco-founder-rakesh-gangwal-to-offload-3-3-stake-in-indigo-via-bulk-deals-124030701163_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fco-founder-rakesh-gangwal-to-offload-3-3-stake-in-indigo-via-bulk-deals-124030701163_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fco-founder-rakesh-gangwal-to-offload-3-3-stake-in-indigo-via-bulk-deals-124030701163_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explainer%3A%20Why%20Did%20Nepal's%20Prime%20Minister%20Suddenly%20Change%20His%20Coalition%20Partners%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07211234%2Fimage-1919.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20dramatic%20turn%20of%20events%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20Prime%20Minister%20Pushpa%20Kamal%20Dahal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheannapurnaexpress.com%2Fstory%2F47794%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520current%2520coalition%2520between%2520the%2CUML%2520and%2520the%2520Maoist%2520Center.%5C%22%3Eousted%20its%20key%20coalition%20partner%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Nepali%20Congress%20(NC)%2C%20from%20the%20government%2C%20and%20inducted%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20Nepal%20%E2%80%94%20Unified%20Marxist-Leninist%20(CPN-UML)%20and%20two%20other%20smaller%20parties.%20This%20move%20marks%20a%20revival%20of%20the%20coalition%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Dahal%20originally%20formed%20shortly%20after%20the%202022%20parliamentary%20elections%2C%20which%20was%20dissolved%20during%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20presidential%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20CPN-UML%2C%20CPN%20(Maoist%20Center)%2C%20Rastriya%20Swatantra%20Party%20(RSP)%20and%20Janata%20Samajbadi%20Party%20(JSP)%20%E2%80%93%20have%20entered%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheannapurnaexpress.com%2Fstory%2F47807%2F%5C%22%3Ean%20eight-point%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20power-sharing.%20The%20agreement%20states%20that%20%E2%80%98coalition%20shall%20work%20to%20ensure%20people%E2%80%99s%20aspirations%20such%20as%20good%20governance%2C%20development%20and%20social%20justice.%E2%80%99%20On%20foreign%20affairs%2C%20the%20new%20alliance%20has%20said%20that%20%E2%80%98it%20shall%20work%20to%20ensure%20a%20balanced%20and%20extended%20international%20relation%20keeping%20national%20interests%20and%20priority%20at%20the%20forefront.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20agreement%2C%20a%20new%20cabinet%20has%20been%20formed%20with%20eight%20ministers%20from%20UML%2C%20five%20from%20Maoist%20and%20two%20CPN%20(Unified%20Socialist).%20Another%20signatory%2C%20JSP%2C%20led%20by%20Upendra%20Yadav%2C%20has%20not%20taken%20an%20official%20decision%20about%20joining%20the%20government.%20This%20new%20coalition%2C%20dubbed%20the%20%E2%80%9Cleft-plus%20coalition%2C%E2%80%9D%20is%20characterised%20by%20the%20predominance%20of%20left-leaning%20parties%2C%20with%20the%20inclusion%20of%20democratic%20parties%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThird%20coalition%20after%202022%20elections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202022%2C%20Nepal%20conducted%20its%20regular%20national%20elections%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20NC%20emerging%20as%20the%20largest%20party%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20CPN-UML%20in%20second%20place%2C%20and%20the%20Maoist%20Centre%20party%20securing%20a%20distant%20third%20position.%20While%20there%20was%20a%20pre-election%20alliance%20between%20the%20NC%20and%20the%20Maoist%20party%2C%20there%20was%20no%20clear%20agreement%20regarding%20power-sharing%20after%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20election%20result%20came%20out%2C%20Dahal%20asserted%20his%20claim%20to%20the%20chief%20executive%20post.%20But%2C%20NC%20being%20the%20largest%20party%20in%20Parliament%20refused%20to%20accept%20him%20as%20a%20new%20Prime%20Minister%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehimalayantimes.com%2Fnepal%2Fdahal-appointed-prime-minister%5C%22%3E.%20Dahal%20then%20switched%20to%20UML%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20newly%20emerged%20RSP%20to%20garner%20support%20for%20his%20bid%20for%20the%20prime%20ministerial%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20later%2C%20Dahal%20changed%20his%20mind%20in%20March%202023%20and%20agreed%20to%20elect%20NC%20leader%20Ram%20Chandra%20Poudel%20as%20president%20which%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20coalition%20between%20the%20NC%20and%20the%20Maoist%20party%2C%20along%20with%20two%20other%20smaller%20parties.%20The%20CPN-UML%20was%20forced%20into%20the%20opposition%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20an%20understanding%20among%20the%20three%20leaders%20Dahal%2C%20NC%20president%20Sher%20Bahadur%20Deuba%20and%20CPN%20(Unified%20Socialist)%20to%20lead%20the%20government%20on%20a%20rotational%20basis.%20But%2C%20as%20expected%20by%20many%20seasoned%20political%20observers%2C%20implementing%20this%20formula%20was%20easier%20said%20than%20done.%20Yet%20again%2C%20after%20just%20one%20year%2C%20Dahal%20unilaterally%20terminated%20the%20alliance%20without%20consulting%20the%20other%20leaders%20or%20providing%20any%20explanation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECauses%20of%20friction%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20intricate%20dance%20of%20Nepali%20politics%2C%20the%20unravelling%20of%20alliances%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheannapurnaexpress.com%2Fstory%2F47806%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPrime%2520Minister%2520Dahal%2520wanted%2520to%2Cand%2520businessmen%2520were%2520reportedly%2520involved.%5C%22%3Eoften%20reveal%3C%2Fa%3E%20hidden%20tensions%20and%20elaborate%20power%20plays.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20pivotal%20catalyst%20is%20the%20imminent%20vacancy%20in%20the%20position%20of%20the%20National%20Assembly%20(upper%20house)%20chairman%2C%20as%20the%20current%20chair%2C%20CPN-UML%E2%80%99s%20Ganesh%20Timilsina%2C%20is%20set%20to%20retire%20next%20month.%20Contrary%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fpolitics%2F2024%2F02%2F07%2Fmaoists-first-became-top-upper-house-force-now-they-claim-chair%5C%22%3Egentleman%E2%80%99s%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Maoist%20party%20refused%20to%20support%20NC%20leader%20Krishna%20Prasad%20Sitaula%20for%20the%20National%20Assembly%20Chair%2C%20even%20though%20he%20was%20elected%20as%20a%20member%20in%20the%20recent%20NA%20elections%20from%20the%20Koshi%20province.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20discord%20was%20compounded%20by%20the%20fallout%20from%20the%20National%20Assembly%20elections%20in%20the%20Koshi%20province.%20Sitaula%E2%80%99s%20triumph%20in%20the%20elections%20was%20expected%20yet%20the%20defeat%20of%20the%20Maoist%20candidate%20by%20the%20CPN-UML%20contender%20laid%20bare%20that%20NC%20did%20not%20vote%20as%20per%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20alliance.%20After%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheannapurnaexpress.com%2Fstory%2F47407%2F%5C%22%3Eresults%20of%20the%20National%20Assembly%20elections%20%3C%2Fa%3Ebecame%20clear%2C%20Maoist%20leaders%20publicly%20stated%20that%20the%20party%20would%20review%20its%20relationship%20with%20NC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20contributing%20factor%20was%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Dahal%20and%20finance%20minister%20and%20NC%E2%80%99s%20Prakash%20Sharan%20Mahat%20were%20not%20on%20the%20same%20page%20on%20several%20issues%20related%20to%20the%20budgetary%20and%20development%20projects%20and%20resource%20sharing.%20Dahal%20often%20expressed%20dissatisfaction%20to%20Deuba%20regarding%20Mahat%E2%80%99s%20working%20methods%20and%20his%20perceived%20failure%20to%20address%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20economic%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Dahal%20urged%20Deuba%20to%20replace%20underperforming%20ministers%20including%20Mahat%2C%20but%20Deuba%20maintained%20that%20since%20the%20ministers%20had%20not%20completed%20one%20year%20in%20office%2C%20they%20should%20be%20given%20the%20opportunity%20to%20demonstrate%20their%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20during%20NC%E2%80%99s%20recent%20%3Cem%3EMahasamiti%3C%2Fem%3E%20meeting%2C%20a%20political%20document%20presented%20by%20general%20secretary%20Gagan%20Kumar%20Thapa%20was%20approved%2C%20stating%20that%20the%20party%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.setopati.com%2Fpolitical%2F162619%5C%22%3Erefrain%20from%20forming%20pre-election%20alliances%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20decision%20unsettled%20Prime%20Minister%20Dahal%2C%20who%20had%20sought%20to%20secure%20election%20alliances%20for%20the%20forthcoming%20national%20and%20local%20elections%2C%20recognising%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20vulnerable%20position.%20After%20NC%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EMahasamiti%3C%2Fem%3E%20meeting%2C%20it%20seems%20that%20Dahal%20reached%20a%20conclusion%20that%20there%20is%20no%20need%20to%20continue%20the%20alliance%20with%20NC%20which%20is%20not%20ready%20for%20the%20electoral%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20NC%20passed%20a%20political%20document%20which%20has%20negatively%20portrayed%20the%20Maoist%20insurgency.%20According%20to%20Maoist%20leaders%2C%20this%20is%20the%20primary%20cause%20behind%20the%20mistrust%20between%20NC%20and%20Maoist.%20Later%2C%20NC%20expressed%20readiness%20to%20rectify%20those%20issues%20in%20a%20forthcoming%20party%20meeting%20but%20Dahal%20responded%20saying%20that%20it%20is%20already%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NC%20had%20also%20been%20displeased%20over%20the%20selective%20opening%20of%20some%20corruption%20files%20including%20the%20fake%20refugee%20scandal%20in%20which%20senior%20NC%20leader%20Bal%20Krishna%20Khand%20was%20arrested%20and%20investigated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENC%20leaders%20were%20of%20the%20view%20that%20the%20home%20ministry%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheannapurnaexpress.com%2Fstory%2F45896%2F%5C%22%3Eselectively%20targeting%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20leaders%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20corruption%20scandals%20as%20Dahal%20attempted%20to%20burnish%20his%20anti-corruption%20credentials%20in%20order%20to%20find%20something%20to%20list%20in%20the%20achievements%20category.%20According%20to%20NC%20leaders%2C%20they%20had%20agreed%20to%20adopt%20flexibility%20on%20all%20contentious%20issues%20but%20Dahal%20dismantled%20the%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20the%20new%20coalition%20emerge%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGradually%2C%20a%20growing%20sense%20of%20mistrust%20between%20the%20Maoists%20and%20the%20NC%20began%20to%20hinder%20the%20overall%20functionality%20of%20the%20government.%20The%20administration%20led%20by%20Dahal%20faced%20increasing%20unpopularity%20due%20to%20its%20failures%20in%20service%20delivery%2C%20governance%2C%20job%20creation%2C%20and%20economic%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond-rung%20officials%20within%20the%20Maoist%20party%20began%20to%20perceive%20that%20maintaining%20the%20alliance%20with%20the%20NC%20would%20hinder%20Prime%20Minister%20Dahal%E2%80%99s%20capacity%20to%20fulfil%20his%20promises%2C%20prompting%20them%20to%20suggest%20pursuing%20cooperation%20with%20the%20CPN-UML.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBehind%20the%20scenes%2C%20UML%20leaders%20had%20also%20kept%20chipping%20away%20at%20the%20NC-Maoist%20coalition%2C%20biding%20their%20time.%20Initially%2C%20they%20approached%20the%20NC%20to%20form%20a%20new%20coalition%2C%20but%20Deuba%20did%20not%20entertain%20K.P.%20Sharma%20Oli%E2%80%99s%20proposal.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20there%20was%20a%20strong%20sentiment%20among%20the%20second-tier%20politicians%20of%20both%20the%20Maoist%20and%20UML%20parties%20that%20communist%20factions%20should%20unite%20to%20compete%20with%20emerging%20political%20forces%20like%20the%20RSP%20and%20others.%20Particularly%2C%20youth%20leaders%20within%20the%20Maoist%20ranks%20believed%20that%20due%20to%20ideological%20disparities%2C%20a%20coalition%20with%20the%20NC%20was%20neither%20sustainable%20nor%20natural.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Oli%E2%80%99s%20dissolution%20of%20Parliament%20in%20December%202020%2C%20tensions%20between%20him%20and%20other%20parties%20escalated%2C%20prompting%20other%20parties%20to%20form%20an%20alliance%20against%20him.%20In%20the%202022%20elections%2C%20Oli%E2%80%99s%20party%20campaigned%20independently%20but%20still%20secured%20the%20second%20position%20in%20Parliament%2C%20despite%20forging%20a%20significant%20electoral%20alliance%20with%20the%20NC%2C%20Maoist%2C%20and%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20Nepal%20(Unified%20Socialist).%20Recently%2C%20all%20three%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20NC%2C%20UML%2C%20and%20Maoist%20%E2%80%93%20have%20faced%20challenges%20from%20the%20newly%20emerged%20RSP%2C%20which%20secured%2020%20seats%20in%20Parliament%20during%20the%202022%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20certain%20second-tier%20leaders%20began%20the%20discussions%20between%20the%20two%20parties.%20Initially%2C%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20leaders%20were%20optimistic%20about%20the%20revival%20of%20the%20Left%20alliance%20due%20to%20the%20prevailing%20low%20level%20of%20trust%20between%20Oli%20and%20Dahal%2C%20compounded%20by%20the%20steadfast%20commitment%20of%20both%20Dahal%20and%20Deuba%20to%20their%20existing%20coalition.%20During%20this%20period%2C%20Dahal%20and%20Oli%20frequently%20met%20to%20negotiate%20power-sharing%2C%20though%20publicly%20they%20claimed%20to%20be%20discussing%20transitional%20justice%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimultaneously%2C%20key%20figures%20within%20the%20UML%20and%20Maoist%20parties%20held%20frequent%20meetings%20to%20strategise%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20new%20coalition.%20They%20believed%20that%20if%20the%20communist%20parties%20contested%20elections%20separately%2C%20their%20collective%20strength%20would%20diminish%20over%20time.%20To%20facilitate%20the%20agreement%2C%20Oli%20refrained%20from%20extensive%20bargaining%20with%20Dahal%20over%20ministerial%20portfolios%20and%20agreed%20to%20allocate%20the%20National%20Assembly%20chair%20to%20the%20Maoist%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDomestic%20challenges%20before%20the%20new%20coalition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20over%20a%20year%20now%2C%20the%20Dahal-led%20government%20has%20been%20grappling%20with%20a%20myriad%20of%20domestic%20challenges.%20The%20new%20coalition%20has%20provided%20some%20respite%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Dahal%20to%20buy%20time%20that%20he%20has%20just%20built%20a%20new%20coalition.%20However%2C%20hopes%20for%20significant%20improvement%20remain%20subdued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForemost%20among%20these%20challenges%20is%20the%20urgent%20need%20to%20implement%20concrete%20measures%20to%20uplift%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20economic%20situation.%20Despite%20some%20positive%20developments%20in%20sectors%20such%20as%20remittances%20and%20tourism%2C%20key%20economic%20indicators%20continue%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.orfonline.org%2Fexpert-speak%2Fdeepening-economic-crisis-in-nepal%5C%22%3Epaint%20a%20bleak%20picture.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20generate%20employment%20has%20resulted%20in%20approximately%202%2C000%20Nepalese%20citizens%20seeking%20work%20abroad%20every%20day.%20Meanwhile%2C%20individuals%20affected%20by%20loan%20sharks%20and%20micro-finance%20woes%20are%20awaiting%20justice%2C%20with%20many%20taking%20to%20the%20streets%20in%20protest.%20Moreover%2C%20tensions%20related%20to%20regional%20and%20ethnic%20issues%20are%20on%20the%20rise%20both%20in%20the%20hills%20and%20the%20Terai%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20factors%20have%20contributed%20to%20a%20prevailing%20sense%20of%20pessimism%20within%20Nepali%20society%2C%20posing%20potential%20threats%20to%20the%20existing%20political%20system%20as%20anti-establishment%20sentiments%20gather%20momentum.%20Given%20the%20ideological%20and%20other%20differences%20within%20the%20new%20coalition%2C%20it%20is%20anticipated%20to%20encounter%20challenges%20similar%20to%20its%20predecessor%20in%20terms%20of%20functionality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20coalition%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20outlook%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20assuming%20power%20in%20December%202022%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Dahal%20has%20adopted%20a%20cautious%20stance%20on%20foreign%20affairs.%20Consequently%2C%20the%20new%20government%20is%20expected%20to%20maintain%20the%20status%20quo%20regarding%20policies%20concerning%20India%2C%20China%2C%20and%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20India%2C%20there%20have%20been%20some%20positive%20developments%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20power%20cooperation%2C%20development%20partnerships%2C%20and%20connectivity%20projects.%20Despite%20Oli%E2%80%99s%20previous%20nationalistic%20rhetoric%20and%20confrontational%20stance%20towards%20India%2C%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20have%20significantly%20improved.%20Consequently%2C%20New%20Delhi%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20perturbed%20by%20the%20return%20of%20the%20UML%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20China%2C%20there%20may%20be%20advancements%20in%20the%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiatives%20(BRI)%2C%20an%20agenda%20that%20China%20has%20long%20pressed%20Nepal%20to%20prioritise.%20Both%20countries%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fnational%2F2024%2F02%2F09%2Fchina-assures-dahal-six-key-projects-will-be-expedited%5C%22%3Eactively%20working%3C%2Fa%3E%20towards%20implementing%20the%20BRI%20implementation%20plan%2C%20indicating%20potential%20progress%20in%20this%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDahal%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20involves%20sidestepping%20key%20contentious%20issues%20with%20major%20powers%2C%20a%20stance%20likely%20to%20persist%20in%20the%20foreseeable%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDwindling%20hopes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20upheavals%20in%20the%20coalition%20signal%20that%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20political%20landscape%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20marred%20by%20instability%20until%20the%20next%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20latest%20turn%20in%20the%20Nepali%20political%20landscape%2C%20the%20largest%20party%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%20(HOR)%20finds%20itself%20relegated%20to%20the%20opposition%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NC%20has%20already%20initiated%20talks%20with%20other%20non-coalition%20parties%20to%20forge%20a%20new%20government%2C%20indicating%20political%20stability%20will%20remain%20a%20mirage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interim%2C%20Nepal%20is%20poised%20to%20witness%20a%20narrative%20of%20polarisation%20between%20communist%20and%20democratic%20parties%2C%20though%20the%20actualisation%20of%20this%20division%20appears%20doubtful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENumerically%2C%20the%20current%20coalition%20remains%20fragile.%20The%20four%20parties%20collectively%20hold%20142%20members%20in%20the%20275-seat%20lower%20house%2C%20which%20is%20just%20around%2051%25%20of%20the%20seats.%20The%20withdrawal%20of%20support%20from%20any%20coalition%20member%20will%20plunge%20it%20into%20minority%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20disconcerting%20is%20the%20erosion%20of%20public%20trust%20in%20major%20political%20entities%2C%20with%20disillusionment%20growing%20palpable.%20Initially%20hopeful%20of%20alternative%20political%20forces%2C%20the%20populace%20now%20finds%20even%20these%20newcomers%20entangled%20in%20the%20same%20web%20of%20traditional%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKamal%20Dev%20Bhattarai%20is%20a%20Kathmandu-based%20journalist%20and%20political%20commentator.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709826322000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07211234%2Fimage-1919.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fexplainer-why